---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
import Header from "../components/Header.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
---

<Base
  title="Warranty - Kanix™"
  description="Kanix™ warranty information including material-specific disclaimers for 3D-printed dog handler belt modules."
>
  <Header activePath="warranty" />

  <main id="main" class="pt-20 pb-16 px-4 sm:px-6">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <a href={import.meta.env.BASE_URL} class="text-sm text-neutral-500 hover:text-white transition-colors mb-6 inline-block">
        &larr; Back to home
      </a>

      <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-5xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-8">Warranty</h1>

      <div class="space-y-12">
        <!-- Overview -->
        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">Limited Warranty</h2>
          <div class="text-neutral-400 leading-relaxed space-y-4">
            <p>
              Kanix™ products purchased through our official store come with a <strong class="text-white">1-year limited warranty</strong>. If your part has a manufacturing defect — cracks under normal use, or dimensions that prevent proper assembly — we'll replace it.
            </p>
            <p>
              The warranty doesn't cover damage from misuse, modification, or use outside the material's rated specifications.
            </p>
          </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Material-Specific Disclaimers -->
        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">Material-Specific Disclaimers</h2>
          <p class="text-neutral-400 mb-6">
            Kanix™ will offer parts in <strong class="text-white">PA11 (nylon) SLS</strong> once designs are finalized. Until then, the modules are not sold pre-printed — you can print them at home yourself from the published source files. Self-printed parts are not covered by this warranty.
          </p>
          <div class="space-y-4">
            <div class="bg-amber-500/5 border border-amber-500/20 rounded-lg p-5">
              <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-amber-500 mb-2">PA11 SLS (Polyamide 11, Selective Laser Sintering)</h3>
              <p class="text-sm text-neutral-400 leading-relaxed">
                PA11 is a tough, flexible bio-based nylon with excellent fatigue resistance, impact strength, and chemical resistance, with a <strong class="text-white">continuous service temperature up to ~130°C (266°F)</strong>. SLS produces dense, isotropic parts without the layer-adhesion weaknesses of FDM. Damage from impact, sustained loads, or chemical exposure beyond the material's published specifications is not covered.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <!-- What Is Not Covered -->
        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">What Is Not Covered</h2>
          <ul class="text-neutral-400 space-y-2 list-disc pl-5">
            <li>Damage from drops, impacts, or forces beyond normal use</li>
            <li>Heat damage from exposure beyond the material's rated temperature</li>
            <li>Modifications, drilling, cutting, or chemical treatment of parts</li>
            <li>Cosmetic wear including scratches, scuffs, and fading</li>
            <li>Parts printed by the customer from downloaded files (self-printed parts are unwarranted)</li>
            <li>Use with belts or hardware not compatible with Kanix™ specifications</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <!-- How to File a Claim -->
        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">Filing a Warranty Claim</h2>
          <div class="text-neutral-400 leading-relaxed space-y-4">
            <p>
              To file a warranty claim, contact us through the customer portal with your order number, a description of the defect, and photos showing the issue. We will review your claim and either replace the part or issue a refund at our discretion.
            </p>
          </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Safety Disclaimer -->
        <section>
          <div class="bg-neutral-900 border border-neutral-800 rounded-xl p-6">
            <h2 class="text-sm font-semibold text-neutral-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">Safety Disclaimer</h2>
            <p class="text-neutral-500 text-xs leading-relaxed">
              3D-printed parts can vary in strength and durability depending on material, print settings, and environmental conditions. These products are designed as accessories for dog handling belts and are not safety-critical equipment. Inspect your modules regularly and replace any parts showing signs of wear, cracking, or deformation. Kanix™ is not responsible for injury, damage, or loss resulting from the use of these products. Always supervise dogs when using any handling equipment. Use at your own risk.
            </p>
          </div>
        </section>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</Base>
